adjectives.description: begemmed (comparative more begemmed, superlative most begemmed)

examples: I  […]  went on down that road which was more terrible than ever now to my bruised, weary feet, but even more lovely than ever in the dying light of the crimson sunset, with all its dark shodows among the trees begemmed with countless fire-flies  […]

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of begem
